WEBVTT

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:05.072
Hey, good morning family. Praise the Lord. Thank you for joining me today.

00:00:05.073 --> 00:00:18.948
I'm going to talk about something pretty hard, but many of you don't know about my daughter and her testimony and the story of what she's been through.

00:00:18.949 --> 00:00:26.276
I thought I'd talk about it because there are a lot of new faces. Many of you do know, but many of you do not.

00:00:26.277 --> 00:00:33.563
For the ones who don't know, I'm going to talk about it because people ask, "What's the noise in the background when you do your videos?"They email asking what that noise is.

00:00:33.564 --> 00:00:48.676
They think it's a devil or something. That's my daughter, and she has special needs. When she was 18 months old, she got the flu shot.

00:00:48.677 --> 00:00:59.009
It's very hard to talk about, but I talk about it because one day I believe it's going to be the greatest testimony the world has ever seen.

00:00:59.010 --> 00:01:08.874
That's what I just keep saying to myself. She got the flu shot and was developing normally.

00:01:08.875 --> 00:01:15.666
Her Apgar scores were completely normal when she was born. Everything was completely fine.

00:01:15.667 --> 00:01:26.478
She was talking and making full sentences, like any two-year-old would do.

00:01:26.479 --> 00:01:29.353
She was starting to really develop and everything was okay.

00:01:29.355 --> 00:01:44.648
When we went in, her doctor suggested the flu was really bad that year and said every parent should have this done.

00:01:44.649 --> 00:01:53.195
As young adults, we were fearful of that, so I told the lady to go ahead and give her the flu shot.

00:01:53.196 --> 00:02:11.918
We got her the flu shot at the same time we gave her her measles,, and rubella shot, her MMR. Within just a couple of days, she ran a very high fever.

00:02:11.919 --> 00:02:24.119
All of a sudden, it's like she went from being a happy little girl developing normally to a child completely in a bubble.

00:02:24.120 --> 00:02:38.554
She lost all speech and just made weird humming noises. She went into a complete zombie state.

00:02:38.555 --> 00:02:50.479
It was so bad that I called the doctor and said, "Something is really wrong with our child."My wife called and we demanded they see her.

00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:54.248
They said, "Oh, she's just having a little reaction to the flu vaccination and running a fever.

00:02:54.249 --> 00:02:59.999
It's okay. This will pass. Don't worry about it."I said, "No, there's something much more wrong.

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:07.576
There's something really wrong."Megan got worse and worse.

00:03:07.577 --> 00:03:16.829
Her bowels stopped working. She wouldn't go to the bathroom anymore. Her belly would swell up to the size of a beach ball.

00:03:16.830 --> 00:03:29.390
As a child, she would hold her bowels for three weeks at a time without going and would cross her legs because of the sensation of going.

00:03:29.391 --> 00:03:39.127
It was so bad that she would swell up huge, and she'd be so impacted they thought they would have to perform emergency surgery on her because of the X-rays.

00:03:39.128 --> 00:03:52.613
It was absolute hell on earth. She started having the worst tantrums and biting herself.

00:03:52.614 --> 00:03:59.568
She would wipe feces all down our hall all day long with what she would dig out of her hiney.

00:03:59.569 --> 00:04:07.265
It was nasty. She would wipe it on furniture, her bed, and our walls.

00:04:07.266 --> 00:04:18.699
Every day I'd come home from work and Diana would be home with her, just weeping because of how bad the day was.

00:04:18.700 --> 00:04:23.441
She would take everything in the bathroom and put it in the kitchen and everything in the kitchen into the bathroom.

00:04:23.442 --> 00:04:30.981
She put things from the bedroom into the living room. Every year when we put up our Christmas tree, she would take all the ornaments and lights down.

00:04:30.982 --> 00:04:39.283
We'd go to bed at night, and then she would put them in a drawer in the kitchen. This went on for years.

00:04:39.284 --> 00:04:47.113
The severity is such that I can't even tell you with words how bad it truly was.

00:04:47.114 --> 00:04:52.659
She would get two hours of sleep at night, keeping us up all night long.

00:04:52.660 --> 00:04:59.725
Diana and I were walking zombies because of how tired we were.

00:04:59.726 --> 00:05:05.758
I would go to work and pass out in the hall because of how tired I was.

00:05:05.759 --> 00:05:15.219
When I was working on a Saturday cleaning the church, I would go into the men's stall and just lay my head over because I was too tired to function, even while driving.

00:05:15.220 --> 00:05:23.047
It was so bad. We would drive her around at night in the car just trying to get her to sleep.

00:05:23.048 --> 00:05:34.754
We had a diesel car and the vibration and loudness would help her fall asleep as we were driving.

00:05:34.755 --> 00:05:43.434
But the moment we stopped the car and tried to take her to her bed, she'd wake up. There was nothing that kept her asleep.

00:05:43.435 --> 00:05:55.471
I would sit in the house and rock her for hours as she would try to fall asleep, listening to Christian music to the point where if I hear those songs now, it bothers me.

00:05:55.472 --> 00:06:07.683
I can't listen to that music anymore because of how traumatizing those moments were.

00:06:07.684 --> 00:06:15.237
I know many of you have children with special needs or autism, and my heart goes out to you.

00:06:15.238 --> 00:06:30.590
I pray for you all the time. People send me letters. I remember those days when we didn't think she would be where she's at right now.

00:06:30.591 --> 00:06:41.523
I prayed and believed, but the doctors all told us she would never progress beyond the mental capacity of a two-year-old.

00:06:41.524 --> 00:06:48.657
He said, "She'll never talk. She'll never be potty trained.

00:06:48.658 --> 00:06:54.214
She'll never have a normal functioning life. You're going to be this way forever.

00:06:54.215 --> 00:07:09.085
Why don't you sign her over to the state and make her an orphan so you can start over and have a normal life?"I told him I'll never do that.

00:07:09.086 --> 00:07:15.855
I will raise this little girl and she'll be healed. He said we were in denial, in La-La Land.

00:07:15.856 --> 00:07:47.117
He said, "I have over 3,000 documented diagnoses since I've started my practice, and I've never one time seen a child like this get any better or have a normal life."He said, "I'm telling you all, you are in denial,"and basically he was rebuking us, telling us that we needed a reality check.

00:07:47.118 --> 00:08:01.198
Diana said, "Sir, you may have never had a child come out of this as severe as this, but we are going to be the first ones.

00:08:01.199 --> 00:08:16.047
We're going to be the ones who come back and tell you that Jesus Christ is a healer and she's going to come out of this."We're still believing that after 20 years.

00:08:16.048 --> 00:08:22.669
We're standing on it and believing for the full manifestation.

00:08:22.670 --> 00:08:39.598
I want you to know that even someone who has the relationship that I have with the Lord goes through things. Not everything is always roses.

00:08:39.599 --> 00:08:55.619
I think it's interesting because we watch other people on Facebook comment about what their child's going through, but I would never make public many things that I went through when Megan was first diagnosed.

00:08:55.620 --> 00:09:04.771
We didn't even say the word autism. I wouldn't even let you say it in my presence because I'm not claiming it.

00:09:04.772 --> 00:09:10.579
I don't have that. I'm resisting what the devil has tried to put on us.

00:09:10.580 --> 00:09:20.411
I refuse to acknowledge it and say, "Listen, this is what we have."No, I am resisting.

00:09:20.412 --> 00:09:26.110
I am resisting it. I am not claiming it. I am denying its right to be here.

00:09:26.111 --> 00:09:30.559
And by claiming it and saying, "I have this,"is not what we have.

00:09:30.560 --> 00:09:39.919
I am the healed resisting autism. I am the healed. She is the healed resisting autism.

00:09:39.920 --> 00:09:45.258
Whenever she makes those noises and those hums and all the things that she does, we don't even notice it anymore.

00:09:45.259 --> 00:09:51.114
We're so used to it because of how many years it's been going on—for 20 years. You just don't even think about it.

00:09:51.115 --> 00:10:02.209
But whenever somebody's watching your video, they're thinking, "What is that?"So I try to explain to y'all a little bit what we're going through.

00:10:02.210 --> 00:10:06.703
The Lord told me, "Brandon, I've called you to the healing ministry.

00:10:06.704 --> 00:10:17.929
I've called you to go into all the world and lay hands on the sick and they'll recover."I said, "How am I going to do that?

00:10:17.930 --> 00:10:26.648
Whenever I pray for my little girl and I haven't seen the full manifestation, I'll be a hypocrite.

00:10:26.649 --> 00:10:51.104
If I've got a child that's overcoming this and we don't see the full manifestation, how am I supposed to go and pray for the sick and then tell them that Jesus is a healer, that you're a healer, whenever I don't even see my daughter's full manifestation?"I argued with him and he said, "Brandon, your daughter does not validate my word.

00:10:51.105 --> 00:11:03.981
My word validates itself. It's a pillar by itself. I don't need Megan's full manifestation to prove my word is true. My word is true and it stands alone.

00:11:03.982 --> 00:11:33.963
Regardless of your circumstances, just be obedient and do what I've called you to do."I wrestled with this over and over again until he kept coming to me and said, "I want you to start a YouTube channel and do these things."I wrestled with it for two years, pulling videos and not putting them on YouTube.

00:11:33.964 --> 00:11:37.963
For two years I did this before anybody would ever really look at it.

00:11:37.964 --> 00:11:47.900
I put a video up for a couple days and took it down because I felt so inadequate, so tormented by it.

00:11:47.901 --> 00:11:59.126
And the Lord told me, "I want you to do what I've called you to do."Well, we went to a Billy Burke meeting—I always talk about Billy Burke.

00:11:59.127 --> 00:12:12.108
It was my birthday, and I went for a birthday present for me. I wanted to go see Billy Burke, and I was excited about it.

00:12:12.109 --> 00:12:18.305
We got there and had to sit at the very back because Megan was acting so bad.

00:12:18.306 --> 00:12:30.655
Before this, we went to Andrew Wommack to get him to pray for her, and she was in the back of the service in this hotel room in Norman, Oklahoma.

00:12:30.656 --> 00:12:42.853
There was a huge light switchboard on the back of the auditorium, and Megan decided she was going to throw a fit and push those buttons.

00:12:42.854 --> 00:12:51.621
In the middle of Andrew Wommack preaching his sermon, all the lights went out in the whole auditorium and it went completely black.

00:12:51.622 --> 00:13:03.938
There were probably 3,000 people in there or more, and it was complete—you couldn't see your hand in front of your face inside this auditorium with the doors closed.

00:13:03.939 --> 00:13:11.302
Andrew was on the front stage and he goes, "Hello?"You know how he's so real country.

00:13:11.303 --> 00:13:15.439
I literally thought I could crawl underneath the table and bury myself.

00:13:15.440 --> 00:13:20.312
That's how embarrassed I was. I was freaking out. I grabbed a hold of her and I said, "I'm so sorry.

00:13:20.312 --> 00:13:24.340
I'm so sorry."It was in the middle of the thing and he's preaching and everybody's looking.

00:13:24.341 --> 00:13:37.063
He turned around looking at us like, "What happened?"When the guys came over with flashlights looking to try to turn on the lights again—they were renting the building and didn't know how to turn the lights on, but they didn't lock them.

00:13:37.064 --> 00:13:50.902
Megan did that. We were looking for prayer. I think he prayed for us, but nothing really happened. Nothing against him; nothing happened. Just being real.

00:13:50.903 --> 00:14:01.350
After it was all over, I walked away feeling so defeated because I knew that I was expecting something to happen at Andrew Wommack's service.

00:14:01.351 --> 00:14:10.394
We took her to that, and that was one of the only services we took her to for a long time because then we had people telling us that she had a devil.

00:14:10.395 --> 00:14:23.171
I told you all about that. I took her down to a ministry in the Dallas area, and they charged us $500 to try to cast the devils out of her.

00:14:23.172 --> 00:14:29.167
I'm not going to get into that. Then we took her to a Billy Burke service.

00:14:29.168 --> 00:14:33.116
When we went to the Billy Burke service, we sat at the very back.

00:14:33.117 --> 00:14:40.115
We were at a massive church, a huge church. There were so many people you couldn't stir them with a stick.

00:14:40.116 --> 00:14:50.718
I was so disappointed because I wanted her to be down at the front and get prayed for, but so did everybody else that has needs.

00:14:50.719 --> 00:15:00.415
The lines were long for prayer and Megan was losing it. She was having one of her biggest meltdowns and she was pushing against me, freaking out.

00:15:00.416 --> 00:15:06.928
I carried her up to the front holding her, and she was resisting me and pushing off of me.

00:15:06.929 --> 00:15:12.453
He says, "Everybody who needs a miracle, get down to the very front. I'm going to pray for you.

00:15:12.454 --> 00:15:25.282
I'm closing the service."I was so disappointed because there were people all around me that had a lot more issues, it seemed, than what we had—broken legs and all these things going on with their bodies—and they were looking for healing, too.

00:15:25.283 --> 00:15:39.570
But there were just too many people to pray for. All of a sudden, my wife comes over and stands next to me with my other two, and Braden was filming it like he always does.

00:15:39.571 --> 00:15:51.015
He films everything. Billy Burke, by the spirit of God, looks over at us and he says, "You two come here."He calls us over for us to pray for him.

00:15:51.016 --> 00:15:54.159
And you'll see the video right here. "Is this your daughter?""Yes, sir.

00:15:54.160 --> 00:15:58.807
Bring her over here. She was making all the noise over there, right?

00:15:58.808 --> 00:16:02.034
What's going on with your daughter?""She got a flu vaccination.

00:16:02.035 --> 00:16:40.632
It caused autism.""How old is she now?""She's 13."So that's the video.

00:16:40.633 --> 00:16:52.937
That was the day that Megan started—the day that Billy Burke prayed for our little girl and she started having bowel functions for the first time.

00:16:52.938 --> 00:17:04.032
She came home and for the first time had a bowel movement by herself and was able to go on the stool and was completely potty trained within a couple weeks.

00:17:04.033 --> 00:17:15.198
It happened within 24 hours, but it was after he prayed for her. Within a couple weeks, God started to restore Megan.

00:17:15.199 --> 00:17:22.859
We were able to start going to church without her freaking out after that visitation from the Lord.

00:17:22.860 --> 00:17:33.731
We weren't able to go into public places—we were not able to go eat in public places or go to church or go to Walmart or go to any of these places because Megan would have such a meltdown.

00:17:33.732 --> 00:17:44.338
We would try to put her in the buggy and as she got older, I'd put her in a wheelchair, to the point where I just sat out in the car because it was so rough.

00:17:44.339 --> 00:17:54.403
We have videos—we took her to stores; we've done it now to prove that we've taken her into places because we want to document it.

00:17:54.404 --> 00:18:03.170
When the full manifestation comes, God alone, with all the documents, will get all the glory for what he's done for Megan.

00:18:03.171 --> 00:18:16.879
One day I was praying and our staff at our church was having a harvest party—that's what we want to call it because we don't celebrate Halloween—but they were having a get-together at the pastor's house.

00:18:16.880 --> 00:18:24.319
Everybody was going over there for barbecue and refreshments, things like that.

00:18:24.320 --> 00:18:37.199
We couldn't go because we didn't have childcare for Megan because nobody really could watch Megan because of how bad she was. Megan would not act right. It was awful.

00:18:37.200 --> 00:18:47.692
So we never really left her with anybody because we knew that they couldn't handle it and we didn't want to hear it: "Megan was this, Megan was that."Oh, I don't care.

00:18:47.693 --> 00:18:52.817
I live it. You know, keep your comments to yourself. So family, even family, I couldn't deal with it.

00:18:52.818 --> 00:19:00.150
Don't want to deal with it. "Megan wet in our chair. Megan peed or had a pee accident in our chair or ruined it."I don't want to hear it.

00:19:00.151 --> 00:19:06.816
You know, I live it. She's destroyed three cars. I mean, seriously, that's how bad it was.

00:19:06.817 --> 00:19:25.270
So when people don't relate and they can't handle something, they attack it or they accuse or say, "Hey, this is what you should be doing."And when you're doing all you can do as a father with a special needs child, I don't need any correction.

00:19:25.271 --> 00:19:32.036
You know, I need sympathy and I need you to love on me whenever you are down and you're hurt and bad. You get that?

00:19:32.037 --> 00:19:38.776
And a lot of people always feel like they have their suggestion of what they think you should be doing because they have it all figured out.

00:19:38.777 --> 00:19:52.611
They look at your life through their little magnifying glass going, "I see that you have a flaw here,"and they have no idea because they've never been through anything in their whole entire life, but they have a suggestion and a cure for you.

00:19:52.612 --> 00:20:04.081
Does that make sense? But everybody who's never been through anything knows how to fix your situation until you've lived it for less than a 24-hour period.

00:20:04.082 --> 00:20:12.709
And even the people who have—this is interesting—the people who have even more of an opinion just encounter you and they think they can fix all your issues.

00:20:12.710 --> 00:20:18.639
But if you lived it for a week, you'd want to hurt yourself physically. You know what I'm saying? It was so bad.

00:20:18.640 --> 00:20:23.098
I wanted to run my car off a cliff so many days because I could not function.

00:20:23.099 --> 00:20:27.403
And that's how bad it was. Sleep? I wanted to run off a bridge.

00:20:27.404 --> 00:20:34.079
I wanted to self-harm. That's how bad it was. I spiritually had to grab a hold of it.

00:20:34.080 --> 00:20:39.936
And the reason I'm still here is because I had that will inside of myself by the Holy Spirit to say, "You can do this.

00:20:39.937 --> 00:20:51.960
You be a father to that child and you be a husband to that wife and you don't abandon them by being a quitter."But there were so many days that I went to an evangelist.

00:20:51.961 --> 00:21:01.107
I had such a deep root of depression on me and I was so suicidal that the evangelist who was at the front of the church saw it on me.

00:21:01.108 --> 00:21:03.838
He called me up to the front and said, "Sir, you need to come up here.

00:21:03.839 --> 00:21:07.093
There's a devil of suicide trying to come against you and I'm going to pray for you right now.

00:21:07.094 --> 00:21:14.265
Jesus is going to set you free."I was so broken at that time. I literally thought I was lost.

00:21:14.266 --> 00:21:19.359
I didn't think I was going to make it out of it. And I remember sitting in the back of that church just looking for something.

00:21:19.360 --> 00:21:31.699
I left early that morning thinking, "I'm not going to go home today."Diana was at home with Megan, and I just thought, "I need help.

00:21:31.700 --> 00:21:36.262
I need help."And I drove to this little town, Crescent, Oklahoma.

00:21:36.263 --> 00:21:47.926
And this man named Ronald was there. Ronald was there and he was preaching. And we had our son at this time; he was just a little baby.

00:21:47.927 --> 00:21:55.931
And I was so down with depression and suicide that I thought there's nothing else I can do.

00:21:55.932 --> 00:22:01.975
I just got to quit. And I went to the back of this church just looking for hope.

00:22:01.976 --> 00:22:06.679
And he called me out and he said, "Come down to the front."And he laid hands on me.

00:22:06.680 --> 00:22:20.260
And I'm telling you, that spirit came off of me and broke off of me. And the power of God set me free. It changed me forever.

00:22:20.261 --> 00:22:29.599
Yeah, the spirit tried to come back, but I resisted it more and more because I knew what it was like to be free.

00:22:29.600 --> 00:22:51.199
And there's so many times when you get to that place of desperation that you don't feel there's a way out of the hole that you're in and you think the only way out is death.

00:22:51.200 --> 00:22:59.279
But I'm trying to tell you today that Jesus has a plan for your life.

00:22:59.280 --> 00:23:20.965
And if I would have done what I was thinking I was going to do back then, I wouldn't be here with my son right now preaching the gospel to you.

00:23:20.966 --> 00:23:35.018
There's a place of desperation. There's a place of darkness that some people will never know until you've been there.

00:23:35.019 --> 00:23:51.455
A place of hurt, a place of discouragement that is so deep and so vast that you don't know how you're ever going to fill that bubble because you think there's no way out.

00:23:51.456 --> 00:24:00.945
And I'm so thankful for Ronald. He was a missionary from Romania and he came over there and he prayed for me.

00:24:00.946 --> 00:24:12.957
He gave me a prophetic word and told me there's people that have abandoned you. And he gave me this word and it was dead smack right on.

00:24:12.958 --> 00:24:22.401
After he prayed for us, then I went and I got Diana and I said, "Oh my God, baby, I have hope. I have hope. This man called me out.

00:24:22.402 --> 00:24:27.892
You know the circumstance."She didn't know how bad I was because I try to be strong all the time for her.

00:24:27.893 --> 00:24:36.850
And I went over and I grabbed her and I got the kids and I took her to this revival that night.

00:24:36.851 --> 00:24:44.985
He was at a Pizza Hut eating after church, and I took her over there and I said, "Let me just try to sow a seed."Because I knew the power of a seed.

00:24:44.986 --> 00:24:55.131
It was maybe like 20 bucks; I don't know because we didn't have nothing.

00:24:55.132 --> 00:25:00.822
But I told her, "Let's just sow that in faith, believing for breakthrough in our household.

00:25:00.823 --> 00:25:24.439
Let's believe for what seemed impossible that God's going to turn it around."I go over this story and I cry every time and it's still painful.

00:25:24.440 --> 00:25:33.120
So Diana got prayed for, Megan got prayed for, we all went home. But I was so broken by it.

00:25:33.121 --> 00:25:41.106
So now I go back to the thing where I told you we were at the party, and this happened right after that.

00:25:41.107 --> 00:25:44.319
That's what I'm trying to tell y'all. This happened right after that.

00:25:44.320 --> 00:25:56.843
So, it was October the 29th and I was standing at the sink doing dishes and I had just come home from work and I said, "Lord, do you hear any of my prayers?

00:25:56.844 --> 00:26:02.367
Have you abandoned me, Lord? Do you care that I'm going through any of this?

00:26:02.368 --> 00:26:16.798
Do you see the pain?"Just fussing. "Do you see the pain that I'm going through?"Just scrubbing the dishes.

00:26:16.799 --> 00:26:22.057
Diana's in there dealing with Megan and all of a sudden Jesus comes in.

00:26:22.058 --> 00:26:39.912
And this is the first time I can tangibly tell you he was not a vision; he was tangible, tangible like this. He shows up in the kitchen. The presence of God felt so much.

00:26:39.913 --> 00:26:55.704
I turned around as I'm fussing and Jesus said, "I've heard all of your prayers."And I turned around and I melted on the ground because I could not stand in front of his presence.

00:26:55.705 --> 00:27:02.879
And he looked at me and he bent over—I can remember his face like it was yesterday.

00:27:02.880 --> 00:27:41.555
He laid his hand upon my shoulder and he told me, "Brandon, I've heard all of your prayers."He said, "What do you have need of, son?"I said, "Lord, don't you know?"I said, "Megan."And he said, "According to your faith, Brandon, be it done unto you."I said, "Lord, I want Megan to be completely healed."And he said, "She will start to amend from this."And he ministered to me some things that I won't talk about, but he loved on me.

00:27:41.556 --> 00:27:51.049
It was private stuff. And he laid his hand on my hand and he blessed me.

00:27:51.050 --> 00:27:57.918
Diana comes around the corner and she doesn't see him, but she feels the presence of the Lord in the house.

00:27:57.919 --> 00:28:04.513
It was so strong and so powerful that it made her stand, holding to the wall.

00:28:04.514 --> 00:28:16.271
I remember her coming in and she said, "Oh my god."She goes, "Are you dying?"because she thought I was going home because I was on the ground, heaped over, just weeping.

00:28:16.272 --> 00:28:25.227
And I was sobbing because the presence of the Lord so filled my house with the glory of the Lord when Jesus showed up.

00:28:25.228 --> 00:28:30.451
