00:51:26.670 --> 00:51:42.479
She went into a complete zombie state. It was so bad. I called the doctor and I said, "Something is really wrong with our child."My wife called and we said, "We demand you see her.""Oh, she's just having a little bit of reaction to the flu vaccination, running a high fever.

00:51:42.480 --> 00:51:47.439
It's okay. This will pass. Don't worry about it."I said, "No, there's something much more wrong.

00:51:47.440 --> 00:51:50.229
There's something really wrong."And Megan got worse and worse.

00:51:50.230 --> 00:51:57.359
Her bowels stopped working. She wouldn't go to the bathroom anymore. Her belly would swell up to the size of a beach ball.

00:51:57.360 --> 00:52:07.279
As a child, she would hold her bowels for three weeks at a time without going and would cross her legs because of the sensation of going, I guess. I don't know.

00:52:07.280 --> 00:52:20.919
And it was so bad that she would just swell up huge and she'd be so impacted they thought they would have to have emergency surgery on her because we'd have to go in and do x-rays, and it was absolute hell on earth.

00:52:20.920 --> 00:52:24.019
She started having the worst tantrums. She started biting herself.

00:52:24.020 --> 00:52:30.219
She would wipe feces all down our hall all day long with what she would dig out of her hiney.

00:52:30.220 --> 00:52:34.559
It was—I'm telling you, it's just nasty. But she would wipe it on furniture.

00:52:34.560 --> 00:52:42.929
She would wipe it on her bed. She would wipe it on our walls. And every day I'd come home from work and Diana would come home.

00:52:42.930 --> 00:52:49.439
Sometimes Diana would be at home with her and she would just be weeping because of how bad the day was.

00:52:49.440 --> 00:52:55.949
She would take everything in the bathroom and put it in the kitchen, and everything in the kitchen into the bathroom.

00:52:55.950 --> 00:53:06.179
She put all the things in the bedroom into the living room, and every year we put up our Christmas tree, she would take all the ornaments down and all the lights down.

00:53:06.180 --> 00:53:13.309
We'd go to bed at night and then she would put them in a drawer in the kitchen. This went on for years.

00:53:13.310 --> 00:53:18.269
The severity of this is—I can't even tell you with words how bad it truly was.

00:53:18.270 --> 00:53:22.919
She would get two hours of sleep at night, keeping us up all night long.

00:53:22.920 --> 00:53:26.639
Diana and I were walking zombies because of how tired we were.

00:53:26.640 --> 00:53:35.009
I would go to work and pass out in the hall because of how tired I was when I was working on a Saturday cleaning the church.

00:53:35.010 --> 00:53:42.139
I would go into the men's stall and just lay my head over because I was so tired I couldn't function, even driving.

00:53:42.140 --> 00:53:48.649
It was so bad. We would drive her around at night in the car just trying to get her to sleep.

00:53:48.650 --> 00:53:55.159
And because we had a big diesel car, a diesel engine, it had a lot of vibration and it was loud.

00:53:55.160 --> 00:53:59.499
So the vibration and the loudness, she would fall asleep as we were driving.

00:53:59.500 --> 00:54:07.249
But the moment we stopped the car and tried to take her into her bed, she'd wake up. There was nothing that kept her asleep.

00:54:07.250 --> 00:54:19.029
She and I would sit in the house and just rock her for hours, trying to get her to fall asleep listening to Christian music, to the point where if I hear those songs now, it bothers me.

00:54:19.030 --> 00:54:23.369
I can't listen to that music anymore because of how traumatizing those moments were.

00:54:23.370 --> 00:54:33.599
I know there are a lot of you who have children with special needs or a child with autism, and my heart goes out to you. I pray for you all the time.

00:54:33.600 --> 00:54:43.209
People send me letters; there was one little boy whose mom sent us stuff, and I remember those days when we didn't think she would be where she is right now.

00:54:43.210 --> 00:54:50.029
I prayed and I believed, but the doctors told us she would never come out of the mental capacity of a two-year-old.

00:54:50.030 --> 00:54:55.299
They said she would never talk, never be potty trained, and never have a normal functioning life.

00:54:55.300 --> 00:55:04.909
He said, 'You're going to be this way forever. Why don't you sign her over to the state and make her an orphan of the state so you can start over?

00:55:04.910 --> 00:55:15.139
You're young, you can have a normal life.'I told him I would never do that; I would raise this little girl and she would be healed. He said, 'You kids are in denial.

00:55:15.140 --> 00:55:28.779
You're in La La Land.'He said, 'I've had over 3,000 documented diagnoses since I started my practice, and I've never once seen a child like this get any better or have a normal life.'He was rebuking us, telling us we needed a reality check.

00:55:28.780 --> 00:55:37.149
Diana said, 'Sir, you may have never had a child come out of this as severe as this, but we are going to be the first ones.

00:55:37.150 --> 00:55:45.829
We're going to come back and tell you that Jesus Christ is a healer and she's going to come out of this.'We're still believing that after 20 years.

00:55:45.830 --> 00:55:48.929
We're standing on it and believing for the full manifestation.

00:55:48.930 --> 00:55:56.679
I want you to know that even someone who has the relationship I have with the Lord goes through things; not everything is always roses.

00:55:56.680 --> 00:56:06.909
We watch other people comment about what their child is going through on Facebook, but I would never make public a lot of the things I went through when Megan was first diagnosed.

00:56:06.910 --> 00:56:16.519
We didn't even say the word 'autism.'I wouldn't let you say it in my presence because I wasn't claiming it; I was resisting what the devil tried to put on us.

00:56:16.520 --> 00:56:23.339
I refuse to acknowledge it. I am the healed resisting autism; I am the healed, and she is the healed resisting autism.

00:56:23.340 --> 00:56:29.849
When she makes those noises and hums, we don't even notice it anymore because it's been going on for 20 years.

00:56:29.850 --> 00:56:36.669
When someone watches a video, they might think, 'What is that?'so I try to explain a little bit what we're going through.

00:56:36.670 --> 00:56:40.389
The Lord told me, 'Brandon, I've called you to the healing ministry.

00:56:40.390 --> 00:56:50.619
Go into all the world and lay hands on the sick and they'll recover.'I asked, 'How am I going to do that when I haven't seen the full manifestation for my own daughter?

00:56:50.620 --> 00:56:56.199
I'll be a hypocrite.'I argued with Him, and He said, 'Brandon, your daughter does not validate My word.

00:56:56.200 --> 00:57:01.159
My word validates itself. I don't need Megan's full manifestation to prove My word is true.

00:57:01.160 --> 00:57:08.289
Just be obedient and do what I've called you to do.'I wrestled with this until He told me to start a YouTube channel.

00:57:08.290 --> 00:57:15.419
I wrestled with it for two years, pulling videos and refusing to put them on YouTube before anyone would really look at them.

00:57:15.420 --> 00:57:19.449
I felt inadequate and tormented. Finally, we went to a Billy Burke meeting.

00:57:19.450 --> 00:57:28.129
It was my birthday, and I wanted to go as a gift to myself. We had to sit at the very back because Megan was acting so bad.

00:57:28.130 --> 00:57:34.019
Before this, we had gone to see Andrew Wommack in Norman, Oklahoma, to get him to pray for her.

00:57:34.020 --> 00:57:41.769
She was in the back of the auditorium, and there was a huge light switchboard. Megan decided to throw a fit and pushed those buttons.

00:57:41.770 --> 00:57:47.659
In the middle of Andrew Wommack preaching his sermon, all the lights went out and it went completely black.

00:57:47.660 --> 00:57:52.309
There were probably 3,000 people in there. Andrew, on stage, goes, 'Hello?'in his country way.

00:57:52.310 --> 00:57:57.269
I thought I could crawl under the table and bury myself; that's how embarrassed I was.

00:57:57.270 --> 00:58:03.779
I grabbed her and said, 'I'm so sorry.'The staff ran over with flashlights to try to turn the lights on again.

00:58:03.780 --> 00:58:11.529
We were looking for prayer, and I think he prayed for us, but nothing really happened—not that I have anything against him, but nothing happened.

00:58:11.530 --> 00:58:17.729
After it was over, I walked away feeling defeated because I was expecting something to happen at Andrew Wommack's service.

00:58:17.730 --> 00:58:27.649
Then we had people telling us she had a devil. I took her to a ministry in Dallas where they charged us $500 to try to cast the devils out of her.

00:58:27.650 --> 00:58:31.989
I won't get into that. Then we took her to a Billy Burke service.

00:58:31.990 --> 00:58:37.569
When we went to the Billy Burke service, we sat at the very back of a massive church.

00:58:37.570 --> 00:58:41.289
There were so many people you couldn't stir them with a stick.

00:58:41.290 --> 00:58:48.729
I was disappointed because I wanted her to be at the front to be prayed for, but so did everyone else who had needs.

00:58:48.730 --> 00:58:56.479
The lines for prayer were long and Megan was losing it; she was having one of her biggest meltdowns, pushing against me and freaking out.

00:58:56.480 --> 00:59:01.129
I carried her to the front while she was resisting and pushing off of me.

00:59:01.130 --> 00:59:06.709
He said, 'Everybody who needs a miracle, get down to the front. I'm going to pray for you.

00:59:06.710 --> 00:59:18.489
I'm closing the service.'I was disappointed because it seemed like the people all around me had many more issues than we had—broken legs and all these things going on with their bodies—and they were looking for healing, too.

00:59:18.490 --> 00:59:26.859
But there were just too many people to pray for. All of a sudden, my wife came over and stood next to me with my other two.

00:59:26.860 --> 00:59:37.709
Braden was filming it, as he always does, and Billy Burke, by the Spirit of God, looked over at us and said, 'You two, come here.'He called us over for him to pray for us.

00:59:37.710 --> 00:59:45.149
You can see the video right here. 'Is this your daughter?''Yes, sir.''Bring her over here. She was making all the noise over there, right?

00:59:45.150 --> 00:59:56.929
What's going on with your daughter?''She had a flu vaccination that caused autism.''How old is she now?''She's 13.'That was the day Billy Burke prayed for our little girl and she started having bowel function for the first time.

00:59:56.930 --> 01:00:06.229
She came home and had a bowel movement by herself for the first time, was able to use the stool, and was completely potty trained within a couple of weeks.

01:00:06.230 --> 01:00:09.639
It happened within 24 hours, and God started to restore Megan.

01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:15.219
We were able to start going to church without her freaking out after that visitation from the Lord.

01:00:15.220 --> 01:00:22.969
Before that, we weren't able to go to public places, eat out, go to church, or go to Walmart because Megan would have such meltdowns.

01:00:22.970 --> 01:00:33.819
We would try to put her in the buggy, and as she got older, I'd put her in a wheelchair, to the point where I just sat in the car because it was so rough.

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:39.089
We have videos to prove that we've taken her places now because we want to document it.

01:00:39.090 --> 01:00:45.909
When the full manifestation comes, only God will get all the glory with all the documentation for what he's done for Megan.

01:00:45.910 --> 01:00:53.969
One day I was praying while our church staff was having a harvest party—that's what we call it because we don't celebrate Halloween—at the pastor's house.

01:00:53.970 --> 01:00:58.929
Everyone was going for barbecue and refreshments, but we couldn't go because we didn't have childcare.

01:00:58.930 --> 01:01:04.509
Nobody could watch Megan because of how bad she was. Megan would not act right; it was awful.

01:01:04.510 --> 01:01:11.329
We never really left her with anyone because we knew they couldn't handle it, and we didn't want to hear about it.

01:01:11.330 --> 01:01:16.289
I didn't care; I lived it, so I told people to keep their comments to themselves.

01:01:16.290 --> 01:01:25.899
Even with family, I didn't want to deal with hearing that Megan had an accident or ruined a chair. I lived it; she destroyed three cars. That's how bad it was.

01:01:25.900 --> 01:01:32.409
When people can't relate to or handle something, they attack it, accuse you, or tell you what you should be doing.

01:01:32.410 --> 01:01:40.779
When you're doing all you can as a father with a special-needs child, you don't need correction; you need sympathy and love when you're down and hurting.

01:01:40.780 --> 01:01:49.149
Many people feel they have suggestions because they think they have it all figured out, looking at your life through a magnifying glass to find a flaw.

01:01:49.150 --> 01:01:54.419
They have no idea because they've never been through anything, yet they have a cure for you.

01:01:54.420 --> 01:01:58.449
It makes no sense until you've lived it for even a 24-hour period.

01:01:58.450 --> 01:02:07.439
People who just encounter you for a moment think they can fix all your issues, but if you lived it for a week, you'd want to hurt yourself physically.

01:02:07.440 --> 01:02:14.569
It was so bad; I wanted to run my car off a cliff or a bridge some days because I could not function.

01:02:14.570 --> 01:02:18.909
I was so close to self-harm. I spiritually had to grab hold of it.

01:02:18.910 --> 01:02:29.759
The reason I'm still here is that I had the will inside me, by the Holy Spirit, to be a father to that child and a husband to my wife and not be a quitter.

01:02:29.760 --> 01:02:36.889
But there were many days I went to an evangelist with such deep depression and suicidal thoughts that he saw it on me.

01:02:36.890 --> 01:02:41.539
He called me to the front and said, 'Sir, you need to come up here.

01:02:41.540 --> 01:02:46.809
There's a spirit of suicide coming against you, and I'm going to pray for you right now.

01:02:46.810 --> 01:02:53.629
Jesus is going to set you free.'I was so broken; I literally thought I was lost and wasn't going to make it.

01:02:53.630 --> 01:02:57.349
I remember sitting in the back of that church looking for something.

01:02:57.350 --> 01:03:03.239
I left early that morning thinking I wasn't going home. Diana was at home with Megan and the baby.

01:03:03.240 --> 01:03:09.129
I just needed help. I drove to a little town, Crescent, Oklahoma, where a man named Ronald was preaching.

01:03:09.130 --> 01:03:17.189
I was so down with depression and suicide that I thought I had to quit. I went to the back of that church looking for hope.

01:03:17.190 --> 01:03:26.179
He called me out, laid hands on me, and I'm telling you, that spirit broke off of me. The power of God set me free and changed me forever.

01:03:26.180 --> 01:03:32.379
That spirit tried to come back, but I resisted it because I knew what it was like to be free.

01:03:32.380 --> 01:03:40.439
When you reach that place of desperation, you think the only way out of the hole is death. But Jesus has a plan for your life.

01:03:40.440 --> 01:03:47.569
If I had done what I was thinking of back then, I wouldn't be here with my son preaching the gospel to you.

01:03:47.570 --> 01:03:53.149
There's a place of darkness and discouragement so deep that you don't know how you'll ever get out.

01:03:53.150 --> 01:03:58.419
I'm so thankful for Ronald. He was a missionary from Romania who came and prayed for me.

01:03:58.420 --> 01:04:03.379
He gave me a prophetic word and told me there are people that have abandoned you.

01:04:03.380 --> 01:04:07.719
And he gave me this word and it was right on—dead smack right on.

01:04:07.720 --> 01:04:17.019
After he prayed for us, then I went and I got Diana and I said, "Oh my god, baby. I have hope. I have hope. This man called me out.

01:04:17.020 --> 01:04:23.529
You know the circumstance."She didn't know how bad I was because I try to be strong all the time for her.

01:04:23.530 --> 01:04:30.349
And I went over and I grabbed her and I got the kids and I took her to this revival that night.

01:04:30.350 --> 01:04:41.509
He was at a Pizza Hut, at a pizza place eating after church, and I took her over there and I said, "Let me just try to sow a seed."Because I knew the power of seed.

01:04:41.510 --> 01:04:45.849
It made me like 20 bucks. I don't know because we didn't have nothing.

01:04:45.850 --> 01:04:51.429
But I told her, I said, "Let's just sow that in faith, believing for breakthrough in our household.

01:04:51.430 --> 01:04:59.489
Let's believe for what seemed impossible, that God's going to turn it around."I go over this story and I cry every time and it's still painful.

01:04:59.490 --> 01:05:05.689
So Diana got prayed for, Megan got prayed for, we all went home. But I was so broken by it.

01:05:05.690 --> 01:05:12.199
So now I go back to where I told you we were at the party and this happened right after that.

01:05:12.200 --> 01:05:15.919
That's what I'm trying to tell y'all. This happened right after that.

01:05:15.920 --> 01:05:19.949
It was October 29th and I was standing at the sink doing dishes.

01:05:19.950 --> 01:05:25.529
I had just come home from work and I said, "Lord, do you hear any of my prayers?

01:05:25.530 --> 01:05:32.039
Have you abandoned me, Lord? Do you care that I'm going through any of this? Do you see the pain?"Just fussing.

01:05:32.040 --> 01:05:38.549
"Do you see the pain that I'm going through?"Just all the things, just doing dishes at the sink, scrubbing the dishes.

01:05:38.550 --> 01:05:48.779
Diana's in there dealing with Megan and all of a sudden Jesus comes in and this is the first time I can tangibly tell you he was not a vision; he was tangible.

01:05:48.780 --> 01:05:52.499
He shows up into the kitchen—the presence of God felt so much.

01:05:52.500 --> 01:06:03.039
I turned around as I'm fussing and Jesus said, "I've heard all of your prayers."And I turned around and I melted on the ground because I could not stand in front of his presence.

01:06:03.040 --> 01:06:08.619
He looked at me and he bent over and I can remember his face like it was yesterday.

01:06:08.620 --> 01:06:14.819
He laid his hand upon my shoulder and he told me, he said, "Brandon, I've heard all of your prayers.

01:06:14.820 --> 01:06:34.969
What do you have need of, son?"I said, "Lord, don't you know?"I said, "Megan."And he said, "According to your faith, Brandon, be it done unto you."I said, "Lord, I want Megan to be completely healed."And he said, "She will start to amend from this."And he ministered to me some things that I won't talk about, but he ministered to me and he loved on me.

01:06:34.970 --> 01:06:41.789
It was private stuff. And he laid his hand on my hand and he blessed me and he was loving on me.

01:06:41.790 --> 01:06:48.299
Diana comes around the corner and she doesn't see him, but she feels the presence of the Lord in the house.

01:06:48.300 --> 01:06:56.669
And it was so strong and so powerful that it made her stand—hold to the wall. I remember her coming in and she said, "Oh my god.

01:06:56.670 --> 01:07:02.869
Are you dying?"because she thought I was going home because I was on the ground in a heap, just weeping.

01:07:02.870 --> 01:07:10.309
And I was sobbing because the presence of the Lord so filled my house with the glory of the Lord when Jesus showed up.

01:07:10.310 --> 01:07:14.959
He touched me. He looks over and he smiles at her. He didn't say nothing.

01:07:14.960 --> 01:07:18.989
And she doesn't see it, but she feels the presence of the Lord.

01:07:18.990 --> 01:07:23.019
I said, "Baby, Jesus is here. Jesus is here."She says, "I can sense.

01:07:23.020 --> 01:07:33.249
I can feel, but I don't see him."And she stood there and she started weeping at the presence of the Lord. And the Lord told us that Megan was going to get better.

01:07:33.250 --> 01:07:41.309
To make a long story short—I know there's some of this I'm never going to ever tell publicly—he blessed me and he talked about the ministry.

01:07:41.310 --> 01:07:46.269
That's all you need to know. Then he said to me, "Brandon, my father's calling me.

01:07:46.270 --> 01:07:51.539
I must go."He turned around and just as he came, he disappeared right out of my kitchen.

01:07:51.540 --> 01:07:55.879
I wept. I look over at Megan expecting her to be better and nothing.

01:07:55.880 --> 01:08:03.009
You know the Bible says as they went they were healed; it wasn't instantaneous that Jesus healed some people—it was as they went.

01:08:03.010 --> 01:08:09.209
That was Saturday. So Monday she went to school and her teacher called me in the middle of the afternoon.

01:08:09.210 --> 01:08:17.269
She said, "Brandon, what did you do to Megan? Something's happened."And I said, "Hold on, Kimberly. What do you mean? What did I do to Megan?

01:08:17.270 --> 01:08:23.779
What do you mean what happened?"and she said, "Explain to me how she's saying words."She said over 50 parroted words today.

01:08:23.780 --> 01:08:31.839
We're talking a child that had no vocabulary at all, was not able to function at all, able to keep eye contact for the first time.

01:08:31.840 --> 01:08:42.069
She made a list of all the words that Megan was saying on a piece of paper and we still have that today. We still have it today because it was a miracle.

01:08:42.070 --> 01:08:51.059
Megan still says things like parroting things all the time now and she says, "I love you,"she says, "hi daddy,"she says, "hi mommy."Those are the things Megan does now.

01:08:51.060 --> 01:08:59.429
She's starting and it's becoming more and more every day—"I want food,""I want water"—things like that from nothing at all to now starting to say little phrases.

01:08:59.430 --> 01:09:04.389
Yeah, it's been a long time, but we've stood. We were so wanting to help her.

01:09:04.390 --> 01:09:09.349
We do ABA and do all this stuff. We put it all on our credit cards.

01:09:09.350 --> 01:09:16.169
We did everything we could to try to help our child to get out of that because there was no government assistance.

01:09:16.170 --> 01:09:20.509
There was nothing really for Megan. They would only allot so much a month.

01:09:20.510 --> 01:09:27.639
So we just kept charging. We kept doing things. So we had to file bankruptcy because we were trying to find her help.

01:09:27.640 --> 01:09:34.459
There were all these different doctors saying all these different things saying, "Hey, if you do this, this is going to work.

01:09:34.460 --> 01:09:47.789
If you do chelation—whatever, they run the IV and they do all the things through your body to pull the heavy metals out from the shots, doing enemas to all kinds of things with chelation or whatever it's called."Sorry, I butchered the word.

01:09:47.790 --> 01:09:51.819
We did all of it. DAN doctors, you name it. We spent thousands.

01:09:51.820 --> 01:09:55.229
DNA testing, magnet testing, all kinds of things over the years.

01:09:55.230 --> 01:10:02.359
It's kind of like the woman with the issue of blood whenever she said she spent all she had but she grew worse.

01:10:02.360 --> 01:10:07.009
That's the way it felt with us. All of these things didn't help but Jesus.

01:10:07.010 --> 01:10:19.719
We went to a Billy Burke meeting and you saw what happened and the power of God came on Megan and that's why we're hooked to going to Billy Burke—because we went and spent—we went to all the big healing evangelists.

01:10:19.720 --> 01:10:27.159
I'm not here to throw any of them under the bus because it's not their faith that does anything. I was seeking the anointing.

01:10:27.160 --> 01:10:35.219
But in a place of desperation—and it was so bad that I didn't think we were even going to be able to stay—God pointed us out.

01:10:35.220 --> 01:10:39.869
God through him. "Hey, you two. Come over here."You watched it. It was just God.

01:10:39.870 --> 01:10:44.829
There were hundreds of people, if not a thousand people up at the front or more.

01:10:44.830 --> 01:10:52.889
And God did that. And that was the beginning of our journey. Then we went to Eufaula and now Megan's getting better and better and better.

01:10:52.890 --> 01:11:02.189
And we went to the thing in Fort Lauderdale. So when you say "Brandon, why are you so addicted to going to Billy Burke?"—because it's the first sign of hope.

01:11:02.190 --> 01:11:08.699
It was the first sign of true hope other than what I had whenever she was at that visitation from Jesus.

01:11:08.700 --> 01:11:13.659
That was a 10-year window. Almost 10 years, whatever it was. It was a long time.

01:11:13.660 --> 01:11:17.689
Plus 10 years before we saw any other things starting to get better.

01:11:17.690 --> 01:11:23.579
Then we went to a Billy Burke meeting and it was like boom. And now it's starting to roll.

01:11:23.580 --> 01:11:29.779
But I'm saying it's like what he always says: God doesn't dangle a carrot. Brandon, God doesn't dangle a carrot.

01:11:29.780 --> 01:11:41.559
He doesn't heal you partway without getting the full manifestation to dangle a carrot and tell you, 'Well, I'm going to do part of it and not do the whole thing.'I believe Megan is a work in progress.

01:11:41.560 --> 01:11:47.449
That's where that all came out of. I'm a work in progress. We talk about it all the time.

